== Characteristic materials ==
=== Isotropic ===

For a linear isotropic material subjected only to compressive (i.e. normal) forces, the deformation of a material in the direction of one axis will produce a deformation of the material along the other axis in three dimensions. Thus it is possible to generalize Hooke&#x27;s Law (for compressive forces) into three dimensions:
